<chapter>
	<title>Chapter 2 Questions</title>

	<section xml:id="sec-chain-rule">
		<title>Chain Rule</title>
		
		<exercise label="chain-rule-matching">
			<title> What's Missing in the Chain Rule? </title>
			<statement>
				<p>
					Drag the parts missing in each chain rule derivative below.  
				</p>

				<p>
					<tabular top="minor"  bottom="minor" left="minor" valign="top">
						<col right="minor" width="100%"/>
						<row>
							<cell>
								<p>
								<em>Directions: Drag one or more <m>\color{RoyalBlue}\text{cards}</m>, on the left, onto a single <m>\color{BurntOrange}\text{slot}</m>, on the right. One <m>\color{RoyalBlue}\text{card}</m> may be used for multiple boxes on the same <m>\color{BurntOrange}\text{slot}</m>. It is possible that some <m>\color{RoyalBlue}\text{cards}</m> may not be used.</em>
								</p>
							</cell>
						</row>
					</tabular>
				</p>
		
				<sidebyside widths="28% 72%">
					<p>
						<m>\color{RoyalBlue}\small\text{Cards}\ </m>👇
					</p>
					<p>
						<m>\color{BurntOrange}\small\text{Slots}\ </m>👇
					</p>
				</sidebyside>

			</statement>
				
			<feedback>
			</feedback>
			<cardsort widths="20% 80%">
				<match>
					<premise>	
						<me> 4 </me>
					</premise>
					<response>
						<md> 
							<mrow>
								\Big[\sin\left(x^{ \blank{3}{3} }\right)\amp \Big]' = \blank{4}{5} x^3\cos\left(x^{ \blank{3}{3} }\right)
							</mrow>
						</md>	
					</response>
				</match>
				<match>
					<premise>
						<me> x^2 </me>
					</premise>
					<premise>
						<me> 1 </me>
					</premise>
					<response>
						<me> 
							\left[\left(\blank{4}{5}+x\right)^6\right]' = 6\left(2x+\blank{4}{5}\right)\left(\blank{4}{5}+x\right)^5
						</me>
					</response>
				</match>
				<match>
					<premise> 
						<me> 2x </me>
					</premise>
					<premise>
						<me> 4x </me>
					</premise>
					<premise>
						<me> \ln </me>
					</premise>
					<response>
						<me> 
							\left[\blank{4}{5}\!\!\left(e^{\blank{3}{3}} + \blank{4}{5}\right)\right]' = \frac{2e^{\blank{3}{3}}+4}{e^{\blank{3}{3}} + \blank{4}{5}}
						</me>
					</response>
				</match>
				<match>
					<premise>
						<me> 2 </me>
					</premise>
					<premise>
						<me> 2/x </me>
					</premise>
				</match>
			</cardsort>
		</exercise>

		<exercise label="related-rates-matching">
			<title> Converting Words Into Math </title>

			<statement>
				<p>
					Match the mathematical expressions on the left to the corresponding statements about changing quantities in a saltwater tank on the right.
				</p>

				<p>
					All quantities are functions of time, <m>t</m> (min), defined as follows:
					<tabular>
						<row>
							<cell><m>V(t)</m></cell>
							<cell>Volume of water in a tank (m<m>^3</m>) at time, <m>t</m></cell>
						</row>
						<row>
							<cell><m>C(t)</m></cell>
							<cell>Concentration of salt in a tank (kg/m<m>^3</m>) at time, <m>t</m></cell>
						</row>
					</tabular>
				</p>

				<p>
					<tabular top="minor"  bottom="minor" left="minor" valign="top">
						<col right="minor" width="100%"/>
						<row>
							<cell>
								<p>
								<em>Directions: Drag one or more <m>\color{RoyalBlue}\text{cards}</m>, on the left, onto a single <m>\color{BurntOrange}\text{slot}</m>, on the right. It is possible that some <m>\color{RoyalBlue}\text{cards}</m> may not be used.</em>
								</p>
							</cell>
						</row>
					</tabular>
				</p>

				<sidebyside widths="28% 72%">
					<p>
						<m>\color{RoyalBlue}\small\text{Cards}\ </m>👇
					</p>
					<p>
						<m>\color{BurntOrange}\small\text{Slots}\ </m>👇
					</p>
				</sidebyside>

			</statement>

			<feedback>
				<p>
					Be sure to distinguish between values (like <m>h(3)</m> or <m>C(3)</m>) and rates of change (like <m>\frac{dV}{dt}(3)</m>). Units and context help decide what a statement implies.
				</p>
			</feedback>

			<cardsort>

				<match>
					<premise> <m>V(1) = 0.7</m> </premise>
					<response>
						After 1 minute, the tank contains 0.7 m<m>^3</m> of water.
					</response>
				</match>

				<match>
					<premise> <m>V(3) = 1.2</m> </premise>
					<premise> <m>\frac{dV}{dt}(3) = -0.7</m> </premise>
					<response>
						After 3 minutes, the tank contains 1.2 m<m>^3</m> of water, but drains at 0.7 m<m>^3</m>/min.
					</response>
				</match>

				<match>
					<premise> <m>C(3) = 0.8</m> </premise>
					<response>
						The salt concentration at t = 3 is 0.1 kg/m<m>^3</m>
					</response>
				</match>

				<match>
					<premise> <m>C(0) = 0</m> </premise>
					<premise> <m>\frac{dC}{dt}(1) = 0.02</m> </premise>
					<response>
						Initially, the tank has no salt. After 1 minute, salt is added, increasing the concentration by 0.02 kg/m<m>^3</m> per minute.
					</response>
				</match>

				<match>
					<premise> <m>\frac{dV}{dt}(1) = 0.1</m> </premise>
					<response>
						At t=1, the tank is filling by 0.1 m<m>^3</m>/min.
					</response>
				</match>
				
				<match>
					<premise> <m>\frac{dV}{dt}(3) = 0.8</m> </premise>
					<premise> <m>\frac{dC}{dt}(1) = 0.7</m> </premise>
				</match>
				
			</cardsort>
		</exercise>

		<exercise label="chain-rule-matching-template">
			<title> Matching Problem Template </title>
			<statement>
				<p>
					Matching Question Statement
				</p>
			</statement>
			<feedback>
				<p>
